fices of the Data Controller, who, as data protection contacts and/or system administrators and/or processing delegates, will be adequately trained by the Data Controller.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The XXX  may also communicate personal data to other public administrations if they need to process the data for procedures within their institutional competence, as well as to any public entities to whom communication is mandatory under EU regulations, laws, or regulations.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The management and storage of personal data collected by the XXX  occur on servers located within its premises.</span>\n<h5><strong>Data Retention Period</strong></h5>\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Browsing data automatically collected are retained only for the time necessary (24 hours) to derive anonymous statistical information on website usage and ensure its proper functioning, after which they are immediately deleted. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For the retention periods of other data voluntarily provided by users, please refer to the specific notices prepared by the relevant Offices.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rights of the Data Subject</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The data subject has the right to request from the Data Controller, pursuant to Articles 15, 16, 17, 18, 19, and 21 of EU Reg. 679/2016: access to their personal data and all related information; correction of inaccurate personal data and completion of incomplete data; deletion of personal data, except for those contained in records that must be retained by the XXX , and unless there is an overriding legitimate reason to process them; restriction of processing in cases specified under Art. 18 of the Regulation.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The data subject also has the right to object to the processing of their personal data, subject to the necessity and obligation of processing for the establishment of a relationship; to withdraw consent, if provided, for non-mandatory data processing, without affecting the lawfulness of processing based on consent before its withdrawal.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The data subject may exercise all the above rights by sending an email to the Data Controller at </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">privacy@ictdomain.org</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The data subject also has the right to lodge a complaint with the Data Protection Authority pursuant to Art. 77 of EU Reg. 679/2016.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For any clarification, the Data Protection Officer can be contacted at: </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">dpo@ictdomain.org</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">¬†</span>\n<h5><strong>Mandatory or Optional Data Provision</strong></h5>\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Except as specified for browsing data, users are free to provide their personal data or not. Providing such data may be necessary to use certain online services.</span>\n<h5 id=\"cookies\"><strong>Cookies</strong></h5>\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cookies are text files stored on users\' computers to enable secure and efficient browsing of the site and monitor its usage.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">No personal data is intentionally acquired by the site.¬†</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This site uses technical cookies necessary for its operation and to enhance the user experience.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This site uses profiling cookies managed by the centralized platform </span><a href=\"https://webanalytics.italia.it/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Web Analytics Italia (WAI)</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> by AgID. WAI stores statistical data of Italian public administration website